# Trivy suppression list for the Bastion image scan (see the workflows in
# .github/workflows/). The PR gate (security-scan.yml) already runs with
# `--ignore-unfixed`, so unfixable OS CVEs never block a build; add an entry
# here only for a *fixable* finding you have consciously accepted or that is a
# confirmed false positive. Prefer bumping the dependency over suppressing it.
#
# Format: one CVE / GHSA ID per line, optionally with a trailing comment.
#   CVE-2024-XXXXX  # reason + who accepted + date
#
# NOTE: The `default-non-root-user` deviation (the image runs sshd as root by
# design) is a Docker Scout *policy* finding, not a Trivy CVE, so it is NOT
# suppressed here. It is documented in README.md ("Running as a non-root user")
# with the capability-drop compensating control.
